                <p><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"><b><span class="spnMessageText"><a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=2556" title="View Daedrea Darksoul's Profile" onMouseOver="(window.status='View Daedrea Darksoul\'s Profile'); return true" onMouseOut="(window.status=''); return true">Daedrea Darksoul</a></span></b></font><br />
                <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"><small>Lich</small></font><br />
                <td bgcolor="#333366" width="100%" colspan="2" valign="top">
                  <table width="100%" height="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top">
                      <img src="images/icon_mi_1.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="" title="" hspace="3" /><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;12/08/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 02:42:39 AM</font>
                      &nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=2556"><img src="images/icon_profile.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="Show Profile" title="Show Profile" align="absmiddle" hspace="6" /></a>
                      &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=11893&FORUM_ID=2"><img src="images/icon_reply_topic.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="Reply with Quote" title="Reply with Quote" align="absmiddle" hspace="6" /></a>
                      <hr noshade size="2"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white">
                      <font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Alright, this has been fuming in my head for a while now.  Yes, this is another topic regarding spells.<br /><br />So, take the current state of spells in PoP.  <br /><br /><b>Ethereal Parchments (61-62)</b><br /><br />Ethereal parchments drop randomly off of mobs in the Tier 1 and Tier 2 zones.  They are now showing up in the bazaar and the prices are dropping rapidly.  I'd expect within a month or so the average price for an ethereal spell would be hovering between 5-10k on Xev.  Alright, great.  Ethereal parchments seem appropriate after the tweaking they received.<br /><br /><b>Spectral Parchments (63-64)</b><br /><br />Spectral parchments drop semi-rarely off of minibosses in Tier 1 and Tier 2 zones, although Ethereal Parchments are more common off of these as well.  For example, Aerin`darr dropped a single spectral parchment and three ethereals.  They drop very, very rarely as of the latest nerf in Tier 3 zones.<br /><br />This was not always the case.  In fact, they used to be very common before the latest round of nerfs, perhaps too much so.  Guilds who defeated Aerin`darr early were able to get spectral parchments extremely fast and the earliest went so far as to start trading spectrals directly for ethereals.  Now, the casters in these guilds have all of their spells and a few have hit the bazaar but are quickly snatched up.<br /><br />Everyone who didn't get into the Halls of Honor, specifically, after the patch, is lucky to have a single spell past 62.  This creates a huge gap between the top guilds and everyone else.  Remember, being in a top guild and leveling past 62 do <b>not</b> go hand in hand.<br /><br />Now, lets take a look at spectral parchments numerically.  Lets say that minibosses have an average 50% drop rate of Spectral Parchments.  Limited to the first two tier of zones, lets see what minibosses we have that have been confirmed to drop spectrals.  In PoN we have Untel`dak and the TM, as well as randomly popping named hobgoblins (lets say two pop).  In PoV we have the sleepwalker.  In PoS we have 3 named giants and a named frog.  Lets say all of these are killed daily.  Thats 9 mobs, with a 50% drop rate that leaves us with 4.5 spectrals per day.  Now, lets double that just for the hell of it from random other mobs that are slain on the server.  Dunno where these are, but lets just say its 9 spectrals per day per server.<br /><br />Now, say there is a 3000 person population on a server that is 62+ but not in the/a top guild on the server (yes thats about right).  Take away 25% for people who don't need parches.  That leaves 2250 people who need spectral parchments.  If each person needs approximately 10 spectrals each (gonna assume dupes are being traded), that means a server needs 22,500 spectral parchments.  At the current rate, that would take approximately 2,500 days.  Seven years.  Is that right, at ALL?  For the naysayers, double the drop rate and halve the number of people who need it and it would STILL take TWO YEARS killing mobs daily to get the people who are 63+ *today* all their spells.<br /><br />Ok, lets take it on a guild-by-guild level.  Say a 140 person roster in a guild that isn't past tier 3.  25% of the people don't need parchments.  That leaves 105 people who do.  Average of 10 parchments person, ya need 1,050 parchments to outfit your current members.  Say you get 3 spectrals a day (probably highballing it there, but lets just say).  ONE YEAR to outfit your guild.  A whole year.  Think about that for a second.<br /><br /><b>Runes (65)</b><br /><br />I have no idea, but I know these are unreachable for the majority of players.  They don't drop in the first three tiers and appear to be rare in the fourth tier.  I have no experience there, so I'll just leave it at that and say this is even more fucking ridiculous.<br /><br />--<br /><br /><i>Now this has all been said before in many different threads.  What new perspective do I have here?</i><br /><br />Well, glad ya asked voice in my head!<br /><br />I was bored today so I went to Castersrealm.  I clicked on the handy archives, went back to October for the pre-release interviews and look at this little gem I found.<br /><br />Source: <a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=4810" target="_blank">http://eq.crgaming.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=4810</a><br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><b>How will new spells be acquired?</b><br /><br />You should find some that can be purchased, some quested, some dropped.  We’ll probably use all three methods. <br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><b>Will we be seeing more ancient spells arrive with the expansion?</b><br /><br />No spells with Ancient in the title for Planes of Power.  But that doesn’t mean that there won’t be rare spells, but nothing that rare. <br /><br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />These are direct quotes from representives of SOE.  Read those carefully.<br /><br />We should find that some spells can be purchased?  Oh, you mean Dark Plague?  Hm... let me look up the word some.  Wow, its plural.<br /><br />Some spells will be quested?  Quests?  In EverQuest?  Hahaha.  There are ZERO quests available for spells.<br /><br />Drops is it, the only way to acquire all of your spells.  Every single one, except of course a single 61 spell.<br /><br />So, lets take a look at their stance on drops.  Surely they don't want them to be too hard to get.  Rare, sure.  But at least attainable, they seem to be doing good with the expansion.<br /><br />Hey, look at the next question.  There will certainly be rare spells.  Ok, we're used to it.  Rare and powerful spells, yada yada.  But there will be <b>nothing as rare as Ancient spells</b>.  Correct me if I'm wrong, but Ancient spells require you to kill in Vex Thal.  Runes require you to be in tier 4+ zones in the planes.  Take a look at your server, how many guilds in those zones have yet to step foot into Vex Thal?  I'd wager to say very very few.  Ancient spells look like Splurt compared to these new spells.<br /><br />What I see here is either a load of lies from VI, or a poorly thought out spell system.  Perhaps it was an afterthought and they needed to put something in quickly.  Obviously much thought wasn't put into it at the beginning of PoP.<br /><br />There are also a few other problems with the current system.  Obviously, you are gonna get duplicates.  The chance of getting no dupes in a set of 9 spells from 9 turn ins is 2.5 x 10^-9.  How bout the classes with 15+ spells.<br /><br />Ok, that was kinda solved by allowing people to trade duplicates although it tapers off after a bit when you need to find the person who has the last spell you need and also doesn't have the duplicate you have to trade.<br /><br />On top of that, we have certain spells that are different levels for different classes.  For example, Destroy Undead is a 64 cleric spell and a 65 necro spell.  Any necro that can get the 65 runes was surely in HoH before the nerf and as such already has that spell from cleric duplicates.  Getting that as a turn in for a 65 rune is a major disappointment.  Same goes for the spells like Greater Immobilize (63 nec, 61 pal, etc.), Petrifying Earth, Pacification (61 enc 65 clr), and others.  Its a major disappointment to get one of these.<br /><br /><i>So what's the solution to these problems?</i><br /><br />Simple.  Put all spells which come from different parchment levels on vendors.  Conveniently, these are mostly roots and other convenience spells.  For a necro, that would make it:<br /><br />Dark Plague (61)<br />Petrifying Earth (62)<br />Greater Immobilize (63)<br />Destroy Undead (65)<br /><br />Four spells on a vendor is not too much to ask, and would eliminate the hassle with getting "bad" spells from spectrals/runes.<br /><br />Secondly, and this is the big and important one, have spell drops correspond to tiers.<br /><br />Tier 1 (PoN, PoI, PoD, PoJ) should drop Ethereal Parchments just as rarely as they drop now.<br /><br />Tier 2 (PoV, PoS, CoD, Lair of TT, PoI factory) should drop Spectral Parchments slightly more rarely than Ethereal Parchments are dropping right now from the same mobs.  Ethereal parchments should be dropping at the same rate as tier 1.<br /><br />Tier 3 (HoH, BoT) should drop Runes from all mobs there very rarely, spectral parchments should drop at the same rate as tier 2.<br /><br />Tier 4+ should drop Runes slightly more commonly.<br /><br />What this would do would be to allow people to achieve spells AS THEY LEVEL.  61 and 62 you spend mostly in Tier 1, working on trials and the such.  You get the chance at Ethereals.  At 63 you probably have beaten the trials and on the way to 65 there you have chances at spectrals.  After that, either you get into tier 3+ with your guild, or you can spend a bit more effort and do the quests to get into HoH and CoD.  It takes a good bit of effort, and the drops are still rare, but pretty much everyone will be able to get 65 spells much like EVERY OTHER EXPANSION.<br /><br />Spells aren't handed to you on a silver platter.  They are still fairly rare and you have to compete for em with your group for the most part.  You won't fill out your spellbook for a good bit.  But eventually, with enough effort, you will.  As it stands now, I have spent a month and a half in PoP exclusively, am level 65, and I have seen a single spectral parchment from a miniboss.  Of course I didn't win it.  At this rate, it will take years, literally, to get my spells, and thats not right no matter how you slice it.<br /><br />Now, people reading this: I know you may have a full spell book.  I may sound like another whiner to you.  Thats fine, you're entitled to your opinion.  However, keep in mind, you got those spells before their drop rate was nerfed.  Put yourself in MANY, MANY people's shoes and pretend you have nothing past 63 right now and you have to start over.  Whats your situation like?<br /><br />Comments?<br /><br />Lich Daedrea Darksoul</span id="msg"></font>
           	</td>
                    </tr>
