                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> There's another problem.<br /><br />You want to treat spells like loot?  News flash here, casters need to fill all the same equipment slots as melee characters do.<br /><br />So, melees have to advance their character in three ways: loot, levels, AA.  Casters have to advance their character in four ways: loot, levels, AA, spells.  Is that fair?  Hell no.  Why do I have to spend that much more effort to get the same return because of my class?<br /><br />You also overlook an important thing.  Focus items.  These are what weapon upgrades are for melee, small DPS boosts (or efficiency boosts).  Wand of the War Wizard for example, increases the damage on ToM by an average of 12%.  Thats probably akin to upgrading to primal or some new poker or something, no?  So then, why do we not only have to get that, but also have to wait for the actual spell in the first place to drop?<br /><br />And spells aren't simply DPS boosters.  A few spells are, yes, but many many spells are the basic abilities that define the class.  Roots, pets, utility spells, slows, heals, etc.   Riddle me this: A rogue's backstabbing ability gets upgraded with new damage tables and minimum/maximum backstabs as they level to 65.  Do they have to gather tokens to turn in to spell vendors for a random chance at getting their upgraded backstabs?  If they don't have the upgraded backstabs, are their backstabs the same as level 60, thereby giving no tangible reason to level to 65?  Does the same go for warriors?  No.<br /><br />This is a fundamental flaw in the gaming system and it needs to be addressed or EQ is going to lose customers.  I'm certainly not playing my necro anymore, but my alt rogue is up to 46 and boy its nice not having to worry about that fourth thing, spells.<br /><br />As for the runes.  Yes, it has been historical that the highest level of spells is typically a lot harder to get than the others.  60 spells in Kunark and Luclin.  As such, maybe runes should be dropping as spectrals are dropping now, off of minibosses and bosses in tiers 2+, while spectrals are very rare in tier 2 and become slightly more common in tier 3 on.<br /><br />Regardless, something needs to be done or all you're gonna have left is the small minority that thinks VI is right in everything they do.  Believe me, this is a small minority indeed.<br /><br />Lich Daedrea Darksoul</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
