                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Runes are going to be unattainable for the majority of the player base for a while. Think Kunark when it first came out, did we have EoT, Demi Lich, Banishment of Shadows, and Enslave Death the first month? No, they were all on high end raid targets ( well what was considered high end raid targets then ).<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Uh... No, Ickhor.  They were RARE, to be sure, but they were always - even since the first day of Kunark - capable of being gotten by one group or even 2-3 people once you get to the level where you need them (59-60 in this case).  The emperor in sebilis is a perfect example of a one group farm-able spawn, as were guardian wurms, though I'll agree with you that sebilite juggs were not doable with one group till Velious for the most part.  <br /><br />The other major difference you forget to mention though is that despite having these 3-4 RARE drop spells, the rest of the spells were perfectly available to everyone - even at 59 and 60 there were store bought spells that genuinely made you stronger as you leveled.  In PoP, there is NONE.  At 65, if you don't have access to raids capable of taking down bosses, you are SOL, period.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Once PoP gear saturates the playerbase the encounters will be easier and the teir 2 rune mobs will be takable with one group much like guardian wurms and the emperor and juggs in seb.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Which tier 2 encounters are you speaking of? Aerin'Dar/Bertoxxulous/Saryn will never be taken down by 1-2 groups IMO, and they drop runes rarely.  As far as I know, the only other tier2 encounter where runes drop are PoStorm bosses, and I'm not sure how tough those are.  <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">I don't think runes should drop from soloable mobs, ever. Again, think Kunark spells, and high level Luclin spells for that matter.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />See my previous point about vendor sold spells, even at level 60.  If they would at least give players SOME upgrades in the form of spells at 65, I think alot less people would be bitching.  The reality right now, though, is that most players will never, ever see their level 65 spells.  That's just wrong - that has never happened before in EQ history, and is just about the most elitist BS I can think of.  Everyone should have SOME new things to look forward to at level 65 - and for casters, this has to be spells, because that's the most basic reason for a caster's existence.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Now those same people ( Not talking about you Daedrea, dont take it personally ) are complaining that they cant get their lvl 65 spells ( and pyre ) because they arent in a high-end raiding guild.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />There is a dramatic difference between offering Ancient/uber spells (e.g. FP) to people who raid in order to balance them with melees and giving casters new spells to cast each level.  I can't see why you refuse to see that.  It was MUCH easier to get spells during the Kunark/Velious/Luclin era than it is in PoP, yet look at how many people are still missing their level 59-60 spells and Funeral Pyre.  Just LOOK.  Now imagine how many years it'll be from now when most people actually attain most of their level 65 spells.  It's sad.  <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"><br />I do agree that Spectral drops are borked now and need to be a bit commoner. They were too easy to get before and VI overnerfed them and made them too rare.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Aside from the Halls of Honor spectral drop rates, spectral parchments entered the game at a rate just fine.  You'd get 1-2 spectrals typically fighting tier 1 mini-bosses and there were camps - hard ones, compared to other tier 1 camps - where you could attain them at a relatively slow rate.  There was nothing wrong with that.  Even if you are right in saying that Kunark/Velious/Luclin "uber spells" are comparable to PoP level 65 runes, how can you argue that level 63-64 spells, which are comparable to spells like the 56 pet, levant, shadowbound, and conjure corpse should be out of reach for most players? I mean, I had my most of my level 51-58 Kunark/Velious/Luclin spells at the same time I attained that level.  The same cannot be said for PoP.  <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="2" face="Verdana" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Good swords drop 'rarely' off some high end bosses.. now our spells do too.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"></font id="quote"><br /><br />Please read my analysis in the rant board on PoP spells versus equipment.  Perhaps it'll shed some new light on this tired argument that SEEMS to be logical, but is in truth alot of BS.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Etadanik the Redeemed</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
