                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I think what annoys me most is that the whole thing seems to be based on the "Trickle down" system. IE Top guilds get in fast and hard and farm those zones for the spells/gear.<br /><br />Once all the top guilds have all the stuff they want the extra stuff that drops "Trickles down" to the market and it becomes available to the "lesser" necros.<br /><br />Unfortunately this theory was discredited in the world of economics in the 80's as it DOES NOT WORK. VI seems to have completely missed this and continues to work the theory. The only thing this does is create an "Uber" mentality and a two tier Haves and Have-Nots system.<br /><br />What happens is you get the Top guilds who are capable of gaining the top gear/spells selling those items on the market and price gouging the other players AT A FIXED RATE. <br /><br />The prices never come down and therefore the "trickle down" never happens as mostly the only other players who can afford such prices are in said Uber Guilds anyway and dont need the items. <br /><br />Top Guilds get richer and are able to buy even more top gear/spells they dont have and hit bigger tougher zones where rarer gear drops so they can start the cycle all over again.<br /><br />I can understand that VI wants to make stuff harder to get to keep you playing longer, but what they seem to have missed completely (and Im amazed that they havent figured this out in the last 3 years.) is that there are 2 basic reasons people leave EQ.<br />1. Sick of it. Nothing is going to stop this.<br />2. Frustration with VI's lies and deceptions.<br /><br />In other words, If I am sick of EQ Im leaving and nothing you can do or say will change that. Personally, if you gave me every single spell on the list and all the best gear in the game I would continue to logon. That is until 1. or 2. happens to me.<br /><br />So by creating situations such as the one that exists with spell drops VI almost Guarantees that that they will lose players becuse they will cause 1. or 2. to come about by their very own actions.<br /><br />Daedra, I absolutely agree with you.<br /><br />Warlock<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49001" target="_blank">Profile</a><br /><a href="http://www.domain-admins.com/Necro/index.shtml" target="_blank">Ulaa's web site</a><br /><img src="http://www.sizzlesites.com/Ulaa/steve.jpg"</img></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
